Interface BulkSynchACC

  • All Superinterfaces:
    RootACC
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    EnhancedACC, EnhancedSynchACC
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ACCProxyAgentSide

    public interface BulkSynchACC
extends RootACC
    Bulk Synchronous ACC. Can act on the ordinary tuple space. Only bulk primitives are included.
    Author:
    ste (mailto: s.mariani@unibo.it)

        Inject in the space a list of tuples in one shot (a single transition step).
        Parameters:
        tid - the TucsonTupleCentreId of the target tuple centre
        tuple - the list of tuples to inject (must be a Prolog list)
        ms - the maximum waiting time for completion tolerated by the TuCSoN agent behind this ACC. Notice that reaching the timeout just unblocks the agent, but the request IS NOT REMOVED from TuCSoN node pending requests (will still be served at sometime in the future).
        Returns:
        the ITucsonOperation object storing the outcome of the execution. Notice due to synchronous semantics, it is guaranteed to store the result of the operation.
        Throws:
        TucsonOperationNotPossibleException
        UnreachableNodeException
        OperationTimeOutException

        Withdraws from the space all the tuples matching the given template in one shot (a single transition step). The empty list may be returned in case no tuples match. Matching tuples are removed from the space.

        tuple - the tuple template to be used to retrieve tuples
        ms - the maximum waiting time for completion tolerated by the TuCSoN agent behind this ACC. Notice that reaching the timeout just unblocks the agent, but the request IS NOT REMOVED from TuCSoN node pending requests (will still be served at sometime in the future).

        Reads from the space all the tuples matching the given template in one shot (a single transition step). The empty list may be returned in case no tuples match. Matching tuples are NOT removed from the space.

      • no_all

        ITucsonOperation no_all(java.lang.Object tid,
                      LogicTuple tuple,
                      java.lang.Long ms)
                        throws TucsonOperationNotPossibleException,
                               UnreachableNodeException,
                               OperationTimeOutException
        Checks absence from the space of any tuples matching the given template in one shot (a single transition step). In case of success, no difference can be perceived with no primitive. In case of failure, all the tuples matching the template are returned (with no only one non-deterministically selected is returned).
        Parameters:
        tid - the TucsonTupleCentreId of the target tuple centre
        tuple - the tuple template to be used to check absence
        ms - the maximum waiting time for completion tolerated by the TuCSoN agent behind this ACC. Notice that reaching the timeout just unblocks the agent, but the request IS NOT REMOVED from TuCSoN node pending requests (will still be served at sometime in the future).
        Returns:
        the ITucsonOperation object storing the outcome of the execution. Notice due to synchronous semantics, it is guaranteed to store the result of the operation.
        Throws:
        TucsonOperationNotPossibleException
        UnreachableNodeException
        OperationTimeOutException
        See Also:
        TucsonTupleCentreId, TucsonOperationCompletionListener, ITucsonOperation, Struct
